# UI & styling

Desktop-first, clean marketplace aesthetic. Extend existing patterns — do not introduce a new design system.

## Palette & layout

- Neutrals: zinc (`zinc-50` page bg, `zinc-900` primary actions, `zinc-200` borders).
- Content width: `max-w-6xl` (browse), `max-w-3xl` (forms).
- Grids: `grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` — desktop columns first, then breakpoints down.

## Patterns (copy from existing code)

```tsx
// Card
className="rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm"

// Primary button
className="rounded-lg bg-zinc-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-zinc-700 disabled:opacity-60"

// Form input
className="rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 px-3 py-2 font-normal text-zinc-900"
```

## UX direction

- Card-based listing grids (Cars & Bids inspiration).
- Clear condition labels, pricing, seller info.
- Success/error banners: emerald for confirmation, red for errors.

## Avoid

- Mobile-only layouts that break desktop grid experience.
- New color systems, component libraries, or global CSS rewrites.
- Generic e-commerce patterns (cart, instant publish) unless explicitly requested.
